<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The assignment "os_proto = 0;" is executed on entry but has no effect: for every execution path that reaches the call to socket() os_proto is overwritten in the preceding switch (OS_SocketType_DATAGRAM or OS_SocketType_STREAM). Any path that does not set os_proto returns earlier from the function. Therefore removing the assignment would not change program behaviour and it is dead code.
</scenario>
